# Registry routing for the @open-tomato package ecosystem.
#
# This file is COMMITTED so that publishing is correct in every environment —
# including a clean CI checkout that has no global ~/.npmrc. Without it,
# `bun publish` / `npm publish` would silently default to the PUBLIC
# registry (registry.npmjs.org). These two lines pin every @open-tomato and
# @bifemecanico package — install AND publish — to the private registry.
#
# Auth is intentionally NOT stored here (no secrets in git):
#   - Locally:  your global ~/.npmrc supplies
#               //npm.heimdall.bifemecanico.com/:_authToken=...
#   - In CI:    inject the same line from a secret, e.g.
#               echo "//npm.heimdall.bifemecanico.com/:_authToken=${NPM_TOKEN}" >> .npmrc
#               (see RELEASING.md → "Pipeline parity").
# Scope-only mapping (mirrors the umbrella .npmrc and your global ~/.npmrc):
# governs install AND publish for these scopes. We deliberately do NOT set a
# global default `registry=` here — that would route public deps (express,
# zod, ...) through the private registry and break installs unless it proxies
# npmjs. Every package in this repo is @open-tomato/*-scoped, so the scope
# mapping alone pins their publish target.
@open-tomato:registry=https://npm.heimdall.bifemecanico.com/
@bifemecanico:registry=https://npm.heimdall.bifemecanico.com/
